trans-unit.source: How do I manage administrators?
trans-unit.target: How do I manage administrators?

trans-unit.source: If you are a Super Admin you can add or remove other Super Admins or Administrators.
trans-unit.target: If you are a Super Admin you can add or remove other Super Admins or Administrators.

trans-unit.source: Administrators can only add or remove subscribers and will not see the Manage Administrators tab on manage.visualstudio.com.
trans-unit.target: Administrators can only add or remove subscribers and will not see the Manage Administrators tab on manage.visualstudio.com.

trans-unit.source:
To manage administrators:
  1. Select the Manage Administrators tab at the top of the page on manage.visualstudio.com
trans-unit.target:
To manage administrators:
  1. Select the Manage Administrators tab at the top of the page on manage.visualstudio.com

trans-unit.source: • To add select Add and type the name and email address of the person you would like to add, select the appropriate agreement from the drop down menu, select the language that they should receive their welcome email in, and select Super Admin
trans-unit.target: • To add select Add and type the name and email address of the person you would like to add, select the appropriate agreement from the drop down menu, select the language that they should receive their welcome email in, and select Super Admin

trans-unit.source: • To remove simply select the person you would like to remove and select Delete
trans-unit.target: • To remove simply select the person you would like to remove and select Delete

trans-unit.source: You can assign subscriptions to your end users one at a time, or using the Bulk Add feature to quickly and easily upload a larger number of subscribers at a time.
trans-unit.target: You can assign subscriptions to your end users one at a time, or using the Bulk Add feature to quickly and easily upload a larger number of subscribers at a time.

trans-unit.target: You can export your subscribers from your previous agreement and add them to your new agreement using the Bulk Add button.

trans-unit.source: How can I select an end date for a subscription?
trans-unit.target: How can I select an end date for a subscription?

trans-unit.source: Subscriptions are always assigned using the best available end date.
trans-unit.target: Subscriptions are always assigned using the best available end date.

trans-unit.source: For example, if your agreement has orders with an end date of 6/20/2020 and another one with an end date of 6/20/2021 the first subscription to be assigned from those two available will end on 6/20/2021.
trans-unit.target: For example, if your agreement has orders with an end date of 6/20/2020 and another one with an end date of 6/20/2021 the first subscription to be assigned from those two available will end on 6/20/2021.

trans-unit.source: If you have a trusted agreement in an overallocated state, the end date will be 3 years from the date the subscription was assigned.
trans-unit.target: If you have a trusted agreement in an overallocated state, the end date will be 3 years from the date the subscription was assigned.

trans-unit.source: Why does my SLP agreement have an end date, and why is it sometimes different for my subscribers?
trans-unit.target: Why does my SLP agreement have an end date, and why is it sometimes different for my subscribers?

trans-unit.source: SLP and MPSA agreements don’t expire, however our portal currently requires an end date when provisioning the agreement.
trans-unit.target: SLP and MPSA agreements don’t expire, however our portal currently requires an end date when provisioning the agreement.

trans-unit.source: We currently use an end date of 20+ years in the future for each order under your SLP.
trans-unit.target: We currently use an end date of 20+ years in the future for each order under your SLP.

trans-unit.source: If you have multiple orders under your SLP agreement from different days, they will have different end dates.
trans-unit.target: If you have multiple orders under your SLP agreement from different days, they will have different end dates.

trans-unit.source: How do my end users activate their subscription?
trans-unit.target: How do my end users activate their subscription?

trans-unit.source: The subscription is active and can be used as soon as it has been assigned from within the Visual Studio Administrator portal.
trans-unit.target: The subscription is active and can be used as soon as it has been assigned from within the Visual Studio Administrator portal.

trans-unit.source: Your subscriber can sign into the Visual Studio Subscribers portal or VS IDE right away, and will receive a welcome email letting them know the subscription has been assigned.
trans-unit.target: Your subscriber can sign into the Visual Studio Subscribers portal or VS IDE right away, and will receive a welcome email letting them know the subscription has been assigned.

trans-unit.target: What benefits and Software is available to my subscriber once a subscription has been assigned?

trans-unit.target: The Visual Studio Subscription benefits page allows you to see and compare the full list of benefits and software downloads included with a Visual Studio Subscription, based on subscription level.

trans-unit.source: How do my developers activate software using product keys?
trans-unit.target: How do my developers activate software using product keys?

trans-unit.source: Depending on what product your subscriber has downloaded it can either be activated by logging in using the email address tied to the subscription, or subscribers can activate it by claiming a product key from the Visual Studio Subscriber portal.
trans-unit.target: Depending on what product your subscriber has downloaded it can either be activated by logging in using the email address tied to the subscription, or subscribers can activate it by claiming a product key from the Visual Studio Subscriber portal.

trans-unit.source: How do my developers get 50% off Azure Dev Test Workloads?
trans-unit.target: How do my developers get 50% off Azure Dev Test Workloads?

trans-unit.source: If your organization has an Enterprise Agreement for Azure, your developers can choose between the $50-$150 Azure credits or 50% off Dev/Test pricing.
trans-unit.target: If your organization has an Enterprise Agreement for Azure, your developers can choose between the $50-$150 Azure credits or 50% off Dev/Test pricing.

trans-unit.source: They cannot use both on the same subscription.
trans-unit.target: They cannot use both on the same subscription.

trans-unit.source: What is the difference between using a Microsoft Account vs Work account?
trans-unit.target: What is the difference between using a Microsoft Account vs Work account?

trans-unit.source: A Microsoft Account (MSA) is a personal email account owned by an individual to access Microsoft services when an organization is not using a managed tenant for Office 365 or Azure Active Directory.
trans-unit.target: A Microsoft Account (MSA) is a personal email account owned by an individual to access Microsoft services when an organization is not using a managed tenant for Office 365 or Azure Active Directory.

trans-unit.source: A work account is one owned by the organization that issues it and is used to access services on Office 365 or Azure Active Directory tenants.
trans-unit.target: A work account is one owned by the organization that issues it and is used to access services on Office 365 or Azure Active Directory tenants.

trans-unit.source: What does it mean when my subscribers add alternate identities?
trans-unit.target: What does it mean when my subscribers add alternate identities?

trans-unit.source: Adding an alternate account allows your developers to access some of their Visual Studio subscription benefits (VS IDE, Azure DevOps and Azure) with a different identity than that which the subscription is assigned to.
trans-unit.target: Adding an alternate account allows your developers to access some of their Visual Studio subscription benefits (VS IDE, Azure DevOps and Azure) with a different identity than that which the subscription is assigned to.

trans-unit.source: This doesn’t provide a copy of subscription to the other account; it only provides the ability to access the two benefits with the alternate account.
trans-unit.target: This doesn’t provide a copy of subscription to the other account; it only provides the ability to access the two benefits with the alternate account.

trans-unit.source: The process for renewing subscriptions depends on how they were purchased.
trans-unit.target: The process for renewing subscriptions depends on how they were purchased.

trans-unit.source: Retail: For subscriptions acquired through the Microsoft Store, connect to the Microsoft Store’s business software section, and scroll down to the Visual Studio section to see the available subscriptions.
trans-unit.target: Retail: For subscriptions acquired through the Microsoft Store, connect to the Microsoft Store’s business software section, and scroll down to the Visual Studio section to see the available subscriptions.

trans-unit.target: Cloud subscriptions: If you’re using cloud subscriptions, you don’t need to renew them.

trans-unit.source: They renew automatically until you cancel them.
trans-unit.target: They renew automatically until you cancel them.

trans-unit.source: Learn more about buying cloud subscriptions.
trans-unit.target: Learn more about buying cloud subscriptions.

trans-unit.source: Volume Licensing: To renew subscriptions purchased through Volume Licensing, please contact your reseller.

trans-unit.source: How long does it take for my cloud subscription to be cancelled?
trans-unit.target: How long does it take for my cloud subscription to be cancelled?

trans-unit.source: When you cancel a Visual Studio cloud subscription, you are canceling automatic renewal.
trans-unit.target: When you cancel a Visual Studio cloud subscription, you are canceling automatic renewal.

trans-unit.source: The subscription continues until its normal renewal date and then simply expires.
trans-unit.target: The subscription continues until its normal renewal date and then simply expires.

trans-unit.source: At expiration, the Visual Studio subscriber can no longer use Visual Studio or any other benefits from the subscription.
trans-unit.target: At expiration, the Visual Studio subscriber can no longer use Visual Studio or any other benefits from the subscription.

trans-unit.source: With monthly cloud subscriptions, cancellations take effect the first day of the next month.
trans-unit.target: With monthly cloud subscriptions, cancellations take effect the first day of the next month.

trans-unit.source: If you only cancel some of your monthly cloud subscriptions, be sure to remove users on the first of the next month to ensure that the correct people continue to have active subscriptions assigned.
trans-unit.target: If you only cancel some of your monthly cloud subscriptions, be sure to remove users on the first of the next month to ensure that the correct people continue to have active subscriptions assigned.

trans-unit.source: For annual cloud subscriptions, cancellations take effect the first day of the month following 12 months from the original purchase, or 12 months from the last annual renewal charge.
trans-unit.target: For annual cloud subscriptions, cancellations take effect the first day of the month following 12 months from the original purchase, or 12 months from the last annual renewal charge.

trans-unit.source: For instance, if you bought a Visual Studio Professional annual cloud subscription on January 3, 2018 then it remains active until February 1, 2019 when it automatically renews for another year.
trans-unit.target: For instance, if you bought a Visual Studio Professional annual cloud subscription on January 3, 2018 then it remains active until February 1, 2019 when it automatically renews for another year.

trans-unit.source: If you cancel at any time between then and February 1, 2020 then the subscription will expire on February 1, 2020.
trans-unit.target: If you cancel at any time between then and February 1, 2020 then the subscription will expire on February 1, 2020.

trans-unit.source: There is no rebate for canceling part way through the subscription year with annual cloud subscriptions.
trans-unit.target: There is no rebate for canceling part way through the subscription year with annual cloud subscriptions.

trans-unit.source: See our How charges are processed topic for additional information about cloud subscriptions.
trans-unit.target: See our How charges are processed topic for additional information about cloud subscriptions.
